CHANGES
=======

- Release 1.0.24.
- Switch Markdown handling to formatting only (no ESLint code-block linting) and add optional install flags via install.sh/install.ps1.
- Release 1.0.23.
- Expand default ESLint ignores to cover .netlify and .nuxt build artifacts (including nested installs) and clean redundant patterns.
- Release 1.0.22.
- Add Prettier prose wrapping defaults (80 columns) to the installer templates for Markdown.
- Release 1.0.21.
- Make the installed lint scripts tolerate projects without CSS/SCSS/Markdown by adding `--allow-empty-input` and `--no-error-on-unmatched-pattern`.
- Release 1.0.20.
- Add markdown linting support and include CSS/SCSS via Stylelint in the installer scripts/config (keeping dist/.output/node_modules ignored).
- Release 1.0.19.
- Fix `installer/eslint.config.mjs` import order so the config linting rules pass without manual overrides.
- Release 1.0.18.
- Prevent Vue-specific lint dependencies from triggering Vue mode detection (so TS-only projects drop the Vue stack again).
- Release 1.0.17.
- Installer now detects Vue/Nuxt dependencies and installs/removes the framework-specific ESLint stack automatically, pruning any extra eslint/prettier packages it finds.
- ESLint config dynamically loads Vue presets only when present, scopes them to `.vue` files, and drops the eslint-plugin-prettier bridge in favor of native Prettier formatting plus VSCode defaults.
- Added workspace `.vscode` settings/extensions so ESLint + Prettier work out-of-the-box after installing the recommended extensions.
- Release 1.0.16.
- Bump ESLint ecosystem to latest compatible releases (ESLint 9.36, Prettier 3.6, TypeScript ESLint 8.44, Vue plugins, importer resolver).
- Add jsonc-eslint-parser and relax TypeScript lint rules so JSON/package.json files lint cleanly.
- Extend lint coverage for .cjs/.mjs files, align lint/format scripts with the new extensions, and reformat configure-eslint installer script with prettier-compatible tabs.
- Regenerate installer dependency list to match published versions while leaving bundle creation to CI.
- Verified installer flow in a sample project (`npm run lintfix`, `npm run lint`).
- Re-enabled @typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any and @typescript-eslint/no-unused-vars as warnings.
